      "message": "feat: \"Introduce Lab app with models and API endpoints\"\n\n- Add a `Lab` app with initialization, admin registration, and configuration (`LabConfig`).\n- Add Django models for managing Lab entities: `LabImage`, `InfraInstance`, and `LabEnv`.\n- Add the initial database migrations for creating tables corresponding to the `LabImage`, `InfraInstance`, and `LabEnv` models, along with model relationships and constraints.\n- Register Django Rest Framework serializers for `LabImage`, `InfraInstance`, and `LabEnv`, including validation logic for fields and properties.\n- Integrate viewsets for `LabImage`, `InfraInstance`, and `LabEnv`, with filtering, searching, and ordering capabilities.\n- Include optional custom actions in the `InfraInstance` and `LabEnv` viewsets for managing instance/environment lifecycle operations such as start, stop, restart, and status retrieval.\n- Add API endpoints via a router for the `Lab` module, covering CRUD operations and specialized actions for the models (`LabImage`, `InfraInstance`, and `LabEnv`).\n- Implement `LabImage` view actions to filter by image type (`IDE` or `Infrastructure`) and list all associated instances.\n- Stub lifecycle actions (start, stop, restart, etc.) serve as placeholders for future backend integration.\n- Add module-level `__init__.py` files to organize models, serializers, services, and views for the `Lab` app.\n\nSigned-off-by: umaru <15875339926@139.com>",
